# Codex Task: Dashboard Formatting Inheritance + Title Rows Section

Review the current Master List Framework source, especially v1.5.24, and update the dashboard-driven formatting architecture.

## Objective

The Format Dashboard shall be the source of all formatting. The script shall only rebuild or repair dashboard defaults when needed. Runtime report processing shall not apply formatting directly except where explicitly governed.

## Required Architecture

Implement this inheritance model:

Global Dashboard Standard
↓
Sheet-Level Override
↓
Column-Level Override
↓
Template Build
↓
Output Sheet Inherits Template Formatting

Blank dashboard override values mean: inherit the applicable global default.

Examples:

- Global Horizontal Alignment = Left
- Column Horizontal Alignment = blank
- Effective Horizontal Alignment = Left

- Global Wrap Strategy = Clip
- Column Wrap Strategy = blank
- Effective Wrap Strategy = Clip

- Global Data Font Size = 10
- Column Data Font Size = blank
- Effective Data Font Size = 10

Only values that differ from the global default should be populated in sheet-level or column-level override fields.

## Add Dashboard Section: Title Rows

Add a governed Format Dashboard section for Title Rows.

Recommended section name:

SECTION F - Title Rows

Purpose:
Define title-row behavior for governed sheets and templates.

Required columns:

| Sheet Type | Row | Purpose | Value Source | Label | Target Cell | Height | Font Size | Font Weight | Fill Level | Alignment | Wrap | Notes |

Required default records:

| Sheet Type | Row | Purpose | Value Source | Label | Target Cell | Height | Font Size | Font Weight | Fill Level | Alignment | Wrap | Notes |
|---|---:|---|---|---|---|---:|---:|---|---|---|---|---|
| GLOBAL | 1 | Report Title | Sheet Definition | blank | A1 | 25 | 14 | Bold | Level 3 | Left | Clip | Default title row |
| GLOBAL | 2 | Date Range | Runtime Month | Date | A2:D2 | 20 | 10 | Normal | Level 3 | Left | Clip | A2=Date, B2=start, C2=to, D2=end |
| GLOBAL | 3 | Spacer | None | blank | A3:D3 | 10 | 10 | Normal | Level 1 | Left | Clip | Spacer row |
| GLOBAL | 4 | Header Row | Dashboard Headers | blank | Row 4 | 40 | 10 | Bold | Level 2 | Left | Wrap | Governed header row |

## Behavior Rules

1. Add Section F to Format Dashboard creation/rebuild.
2. Do not overwrite user-entered Section F values unless a full reset is explicitly requested.
3. Template builders shall read title-row configuration from Section F.
4. If Section F is missing or blank, fall back to the governed global standards:
  - Row 1 height 25, Level 3, Arial 14 bold
  - Row 2 height 20, Level 3, Arial 10
  - Row 3 height 10, Level 1
  - Row 4 height 40, Level 2, Arial 10 bold, wrap
5. Column-level dashboard fields may remain blank when global defaults apply.
6. Sheet-level and column-level values are overrides only.
7. Runtime processing functions shall not reformat title rows after output creation.
8. Output sheets shall inherit title-row formatting from verified templates.

